snippet.textDisplay:
I had so many thoughts and feelings flowing through my heart and mind as I watched this, ranging from the amusement of how embarrassed a generic YouTube troll must feel (back right before they announced TCW's return, there was some jerk going around saying "Your KIDS show isn't coming back! DEAL WITH IT!"), to how I cannot believe that something so special to me, from when I was a child of 10 or so to a guy in his 20's, is coming back for a grand finale and is looking more amazing than it ever did before.


I don't want to hear anybody else ever whine about how Disney doesn't listen to its fans or Disney doesn't do this or that - this revival (as well as stuff like Battlefront 2 going from worst to one of the best Star Wars games instead of the devs just taking the money and leaving it to waste away) is proof positive that they do in fact listen and care. If they don't, then explain this trailer to me. I'm not kissing up to them but the fact that they brought my childhood back and are giving it tons of TLC to make it as incredible and satisfying as it possibly can be has long since earned my respect.


I'm subbing to Disney+ in February, just for this.
